<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 01 at 10:43PM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>Mild air now over the region will keep precipitation in the form
of rain well into the night. After 4 AM, colder air will slowly
advance across the area from the northwest. This will turn the
rain over to all snow. Locations along the far east from Monroe up
through the city of Detroit to Port Huron will see this transition
to snow occur around or shortly after 7 AM. Once the snow begins,
falling temperatures and wet snow will cause lead to very slippery
conditions on untreated surfaces.</description>
